description:
secretx-core/src/lib.rs:1097: SecretUri derives Debug but not Display. Code that wants to log a URI uses {:?} which produces the struct-debug form (SecretUri { backend: "env", path: "X", params: {} }) rather than the source-form 'secretx:env:X'.

Idiomatic Rust: a URI type should have Display that produces a parseable URI. SecretUri::parse(format!("{}", uri)) should round-trip.

Fix:
    impl fmt::Display for SecretUri {
        fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
            write!(f, "secretx:{}:{}", self.backend, percent_encode(&self.path))?;
            if !self.params.is_empty() {
                f.write_char('?')?;
                let mut first = true;
                for (k, v) in &self.params {
                    if !first { f.write_char('&')?; }
                    write!(f, "{}={}", percent_encode(k), percent_encode(v))?;
                    first = false;
                }
            }
            Ok(())
        }
    }
Note this requires a percent_encode counterpart to the existing percent_decode (lib.rs:1022). The encoder is the trickier half — it needs to know which characters to escape (RFC 3986 unreserved set).

P2 because nobody's blocked on it today; logs use {:?} and that's fine until the URI ends up in user-facing output.
